on directly unless it’s through the public API. Loading `HazelcastIMapAdapter` in an isolated classloader with a different classpath could mean direct classloading, which might not be acceptable. I need to find a better method to avoid potential issues with class loading and reflection.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering coverage in build.gradle**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the final build should include high coverage, but does it need both elements? I wonder if I need to inspect the build.gradle dependencies to see what might be included. Maybe it’s necessary to read through the existing file from our changes to adapt accordingly. It feels like there’s something crucial in there that I don't want to overlook, so I'll take a closer look.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_H5F3UskOJD4de9GHAN3mbp9L|fc_0f8b2de55a1680c70169f56f092da48193b6d00ffcf5b33f59", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build.gradle", "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 37297, "output": 982, "cacheRead": 6144, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44423, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777692409615, "responseId": "resp_0f8b2de55a1680c70169f56efa8c948193af21a22266770e16"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_H5F3UskOJD4de9GHAN3mbp9L|fc_0f8b2de55a1680c70169f56f092da48193b6d00ffcf5b33f59", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\nplugins {\n    id \"org.graalvm.internal.tck\"\n}\n\nString libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\ndependencies {\n    testImplementation \"io.micrometer:micrometer-core:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplement