[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering classloader behavior**\n\nI'm thinking about the interaction between the normal classloader and the fallback mechanisms. In the primary classloader from HC4, it exists, but the fallback is absent. However, in a child classloader scenario, it seems like it can hide the primary class. In this case, the fallback might be able to access a \"fake legacy\" from the parent if it's compiled within the test classes. It’s quite a nuanced situation!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f8b2de55a1680c70169f5700cab3c8193b9f74971ed9a0ba7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9XAluRpHkDFnolnHKytRJohlHkx27z0poj54dVdBuemvgCllHpcicxLaHxkbrQ9u3sTLTMGU54U68951VNxEfBQqYrBqKax6V79QRWsB37d2PrIjwmDYp5DVZGjSzHMNLtZZcMIueIpJQMoG6KY-dMZ5ilm5KetQkpMU-OK85NPyOWouQ2I-Av0Ec8b2N0TYH1f3WvEjxghiu0hrnESEQ70Is3QsqYuHNi74baEgDhFQ2EblKQLRmaXz8Ysio_1vJ24oBTda6ZjfYfRqmb2CwEqq6wWGVFYIfoY9rMCjGdiMtBeJ8v10sX6EUDTcGvsXpcL0q2hFOBQKDlQKYgbOI5atw3JLPwG_qPsa9j2HX4ohCQcAKaxxo7ZE06KQI13sM4nf7GKapg-DQE8K6-sFycTTvdGDKRMeTsARuw6aa6tKhB2lrOGgLkvVBb0b51Ev-as6uxgDHD7SUIzVs0QBEz6espIq3I9LycyoZHQmuSJj0TGBQTsYggO_Ip_xVLKZ5-zAAbPgp3AkiMryg-wJGaMHykqfB_gvdqELq9V6KjcukQ4u-_FL8_KYNoKwAVcS5GcyPIpq_3OnwZVTqGHRQu12iLdJKT1V_14I-WOYlYMScl5UmYasI09mPKzwcVTRNcJPQwZOqYLcxOEUIthpWafSggInjERrtO5ACGXGBUu8ZMiRAE8HHJEgH9RoYuLnTS-CF9znHIaOl6g3gAMa8lofliqmB7H2u1GsMzXJlf4VYCmqpJRWwP3H9XJ0re-tcrM6EWtXgYBNh6VGxDlUFr8HuR0XCDCMr99s0bBIHoC0Iplr1GwwVlGStb6bvuU6wPnbMSqG-ZiTTndaQgOhMwOdqc284r4KYcCYRNN41i24Uzbf7mRp2v_gaRFb6yszzXpg3luO95HRf0mJYfzzSWIMOIyvxGe11AOfQHd2kr1Ervx4nizUVBUIsgobUiDM0qYe1yaL_65VM_j-Je-IM-N08RdDbxWHp9KeeCsaQQG030dme5Jr1KJJFZMfKCbLkGsNr9Uvk7gwbuL8pN3iQHyP-R4lyg9-GF8vT_E9Xc6Zot1gXImiq4KQhXpSUzMNtH0F2hu_Pp-sgmdIJDmRYXF5eE4bFGNOJEEYKTP1YrazR1kGwJiHbyvJwz8tA5cp5qvNnZ4xr6sSj029xE7AzZI-TgpzDIABSgUiIHvahRhxST8-gNmIflb0kQCrV1D3S2VaNKCMIjokdWEZyx-4IJiS4JRDLImTM9MQyAxRwoLs6uJHBxkOA42Xfx1hvhy-QV3lYcTedx2