[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Java Class Loading**\n\nI'm considering modifications in the build.gradle file, specifically adding `testImplementation 'com.hazelcast:hazelcast:4.2.8'` and creating a custom configuration for the HC3 jar path. In the test class, I think of using `URLClassLoader` with both HC3 jar and test/classes. But then, I'm wondering if the adapter's child loader should use the parent loader. If the parent has HC4 as primary, it might hide HC3, yet with URLClassLoader, I can load legacy classes from URL effectively.\n\n**Exploring class instrumentation**\n\nI'm considering the same source class being defined separately. I wonder if dynamic tracking might be able to instrument it. It could potentially track library classes on the classpath, but if we define class bytes ourselves from resources, maybe the instrumentation won't work. It seems like there are complexities to work through here, and I'm curious about how that all interacts! There's definitely a lot to think about in terms of definitions and resources.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f8b2de55a1680c70169f5702802bc8193a8431875f096cf66\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9XA9ffpXcjx1YhmYsuRztRrTUuq7cRHfEEPhg9P56q4ssoSbNE-QqFi9D5ED9JWN8hFFnEjMNPVV335_uvYPTrDOhCw_RvMydslobUwpYcBmI1CV5SP6js99Kq5oLfX3pFEGcMSl7DOegQioLlXbzBWi22Ctxm2QLoM2fXra5WXbJ40cOoB5SZ8JeuUDwfqcoPdYxV_6OlmuY1nbjRZ2vyafnZCLzKiVl137ztJQp9HuDsNNrgToqvH7XX5d9MAY0FBpXjVvSvtEH565RkZKL2OiieJUt9201a--b19QHPGD6QxUGPrcZO5G9EUm4gpyouVpikbkjUzfrPQiLeBZBduQKSNyQmPaN5gfbH_9EioJ2vRoNGDShddEdQBOix4rz8easYZRX-oxLwMzzd3LnjKCMEgZ2jKzZ_mn6b-jRUP_pglVtNSS481H6RUn86Vb0Keei9zA62dcXeoAlul1R3ToBy-DHUwnK1f7y19ifyVic-YQlupmY9O0zrUDpCkl0DhLCGGIOeQnYDWDm6peefcA0edcsmJ1pYcdYmTAgwLMQnlKxa-NLjWF6bFz0hy4zYLs82Vo-BmQxnHiUyNlsjdu-FSsjODbMZvxQH87RTa9WpB31nGMDL3d7G6zPUa0TzmbfpN_QNgNXzc-z7cnpb4QCgY9yXve8YRG2ODCwVaxt1mMI8Z_9gPsOXaaKVbe6k8gLkQRZigS4h